mention_imgdesc_Azure.OCR text: JOHN TANSY is a phenomenal youngster. He was literally bred; in the bone. His mother, Emma Purcell, is an; actress, and was a well-known child player.; She was the first "Wang" baby with De Wolf; Hopper. She went to a convent school, and; was the star of the school plays. J. M. Hill, of; the Union Square Theatre, saw her in a school; play, and put her into child rôles in his theatre.; John's father is Harry Tansy, a comedian,; playing this season with "Texas." In the Car-; lotta Nillson company, because of his blasé man-; ner and six years' experience, they call Johnny; JOHN TANSY; "The Veteran Actor." He was two years'; old when he began playing. He made his; début with N. C. Goodwin in "Wolfville." Miss Katherine Grey; was the leading woman of that company, and Miss Grey has al-; ways remembered the clever child, for on the opening night of; every new production she sends John a telegram. He played next; with Robert Peyton Gibbs in "The Land of the Free." He was; seen in a revival of "Wang." Then followed a season of thirty-; nine weeks with Olga Nethersole. He followed the dramatic; flag of Nanette Comstock next in "Jet." Alfred Bruening was; the next star, and the play "The Right to; Live."
